                    <p>Without Javascript your site won't be very interactive, javascript is responsible for everything from modals, slideshows, animation, ajax content loading, I could go on and on.</p><p>I've been writing javascript for over 10 years now, and use the jQuery library to handle cross browser support and the vast library of plugins the community has created. This gives me the ability to make a completely custom site much faster then if I had written it without the jQuery library.</p>
